## ICT Daily Bias — Corrected

The logic is simple:[^8_1]

- Look at the **2nd to last closed candle** — its full range (high to low, wicks included) is your reference zone.
- If the **last closed candle closes ABOVE that candle's high** → **Bullish bias** — expect price to continue up.[^8_1]
- If the **last closed candle closes BELOW that candle's low** → **Bearish bias** — expect price to continue down.[^8_1]
- If it closes **inside** the range → no bias (ranging, signal is ignored).[^8_1]

That's it. One candle breaks out of the previous candle's full range on a **close basis** — wicks don't count for the trigger, only the close. The direction of that breakout is your bias for the session.

