- Now the script demands that **10 bars to the left** are all lower than the pivot
- This **filters out all the small bumps** — only the truly dominant highs qualify
- Your 74 RSI high is now the only valid Pivot 1 in that window
- Your 71 RSI high becomes the valid Pivot 2
- Divergence fires ✅


## The Insight

**lbL is actually your quality filter**, not lbR. It controls *how significant* a pivot must be:

- Low lbL (3–5) = catches minor swings, lots of noise
- High lbL (10+) = only catches major dominant swings, cleaner signals


