# in order to capture all the potnetial divergences long and short distance, what would be your recomentaditon for the 4 passes?

Here's my recommended setup for covering all divergence distances systematically:

## The Logic Behind the Setup

You want to cover 4 "zones" of divergence distance — ultra-short, short, medium, and long. Each pass should have a **lbL that matches the distance** — bigger distance needs bigger lbL to avoid picking up intermediate pivots as we discovered earlier.[^22_1]

## Recommended 4 Pass Configuration

|  | Pass 1 — Ultra Short | Pass 2 — Short | Pass 3 — Medium | Pass 4 — Long |
| :-- | :-- | :-- | :-- | :-- |
| **lbL** | 3 | 5 | 10 | 20 |
| **lbR** | 1 | 1 | 2 | 3 |
| **Min Bars** | 2 | 5 | 15 | 40 |
| **Max Bars** | 15 | 40 | 80 | 200 |
| **Line Width** | 1 | 1 | 2 | 3 |
| **Use Case** | Scalp / quick setups | Intraday swings | Swing trades | Position trades |

## Why These Specific Values

- **lbL scales up with distance** — the further apart the pivots, the more dominant they need to be to avoid false pairs (your exact discovery earlier)
- **lbR stays small (1–3)** — keeps signals timely across all passes
- **Min/Max ranges don't overlap much** — each pass has its own exclusive zone so you don't get 3 passes firing on the same divergence simultaneously
- **Line width increases with distance** — visually heavier lines for bigger, more significant setups


## Color Suggestion

| Pass | Bull Color | Bear Color |
| :-- | :-- | :-- |
| Pass 1 — Ultra Short | Light green `#69f0ae` | Light red `#ff8a80` |
| Pass 2 — Short | Medium green `#00e676` | Medium red `#ff1744` |
| Pass 3 — Medium | Strong green `#00c853` | Strong red `#d50000` |
| Pass 4 — Long | Gold `#ffd600` | Purple `#aa00ff` |

The color intensity **increases with pass importance** — so at a glance, brighter/darker lines = bigger timeframe divergence. Gold and purple for Pass 4 make long-term setups stand out immediately from the short-term noise.

